description: Unique identifier for each patient. Any rows associated with a single subject_id pertain to the same individual.
Unique identifier for a single patient's admission to the hospital. Represents a single hospitalization encounter.
Unique identifier for an ICU stay. Generated identifier derived from transfers table.
Genotypical sex of the patient (M = Male; F = Female)
De-identified date of death. Extracted from hospital records and Massachusetts State Registry of Vital Records. Censored at one year after last hospital discharge.
Date and time the patient was admitted to the hospital
Date and time the patient was discharged from the hospital
Length of stay in the hospital measured in days
Age of the patient at the time of hospital admission
source: Derived from patients and admissions tables

description: Self-reported race/ethnicity of the patient
Binary flag indicating whether patient died during hospitalization (1 = died; 0 = survived to discharge)
Sequential number of the hospital stay for this patient (chronologically ordered)
Boolean indicating if this is the patient's first hospital stay in the database
Date and time the patient was transferred into the ICU
Date and time the patient was transferred out of the ICU
Length of stay in the ICU measured in fractional days
Sequential number of the ICU stay for this patient within a hospitalization
Boolean indicating if this is the patient's first ICU stay in the hospitalization
Duplicate of admittime - hospital admission date and time
Duplicate of dischtime - hospital discharge date and time
Time of in-hospital death. Only present if patient died in hospital.
Type of admission classifying urgency (AMBULATORY OBSERVATION; DIRECT EMER.; ELECTIVE; URGENT; etc.)
